Car Fuel Efficiency Prediction using Machine Learning

1. Introduction
Fuel efficiency is a key factor in automotive engineering. This project focuses on predicting fuel efficiency of a vehicle using machine learning models.

2. Problem Statement
The objective is to predict the miles per gallon (MPG) of a vehicle based on its specifications such as engine size, weight, horsepower, and cylinders.

3. Importance of the Problem
Improving fuel efficiency reduces fuel consumption and environmental impact. Accurate prediction helps engineers design optimized vehicles.

4. Methodology
A regression-based machine learning model (Linear Regression) was used. The dataset was split into training and testing sets. The model was trained and evaluated using Mean Squared Error and R2 Score.

5. Tools and Technologies
Python programming language, Pandas for data handling, NumPy for numerical operations, and Scikit-learn for machine learning.

6. Challenges Faced
Understanding feature relationships, preparing structured data, and evaluating model performance were key challenges.

7. Results
The model successfully predicts MPG values with reasonable accuracy based on input vehicle features.

8. Learning Outcomes
This project improved understanding of regression models, dataset handling, model training, testing, and evaluation.

9. Future Improvements
Future improvements include using real-world datasets, trying advanced models like Random Forest, and creating a graphical interface.
